Central America and South America are presented as two different continents in the initial data frame. However since Central America only includes 4 entries it makes sense to move its entries such that they belong to South America.

EDA

# Changing Central America entries to South America across data frames
nations$Cont[c(203, 209, 249, 268)] <- "South America"
nations_disc$Cont[c(203, 209, 249, 268)] <- "South America"
table(nations$Cont)

##        Africa          Asia        Europe   Middle East North America

# number of country entries per continent 
cont_count_sum <- list()
for (i in (1:length(unique(nations$Cont)))){
  curr_cont <- unique(nations$Cont)[i]
  curr_cont_df <- nations[nations$Cont == curr_cont,]
  cntry_df <- data.frame(table(curr_cont_df$Cntry))
  cont_count_sum[[i]] <- cntry_df
  names(cont_count_sum[[i]]) = curr_cont
}

# IQR for each variable and the corresponding outliers
for (col in colnames(nations_numeric)){
  Q <- quantile(nations_numeric[[col]], probs=c(.25, .75), na.rm = FALSE)
  iqr <- IQR(nations_numeric[[col]])
  up <- Q[2]+1.5*iqr # Upper Range  
  low <- Q[1]-1.5*iqr # Lower Range
  print(paste0(col, ": Lowerbound - ", low, "; Upperbound - ", up))
  criteria <- nations_numeric[[col]] > up | nations_numeric[[col]] < low
  if (col %in% c("COL2", "Rent", "COLRent", "Groc", "Restnt", "PurPow")){
    print(paste0("Outliers for ", col, ": ", sum(criteria), 
                 "; Unique cities: ", 
                 paste(unique(nations$City[criteria]), collapse = ", ")))
  } else {
    print(paste0("Outliers for ", col, ": ", sum(criteria), 
                 "; Unique contries: ", 
                 paste(unique(nations$Cntry[criteria]), collapse = ", ")))
  }

}

Cluster Analysis

#https://www.r-bloggers.com/2021/04/cluster-analysis-in-r/

#K-means
means <- apply(nations_numeric,2,mean)
sds <- apply(nations_numeric,2,sd)
nor <- scale(nations_numeric,center=means,scale=sds)

wss <- (nrow(nor)-1)*sum(apply(nor,2,var))
for (i in 2:20) wss[i] <- sum(kmeans(nor, centers=i)$withinss)
plot(1:20, wss, type="b", xlab="Number of Clusters", ylab="Within groups sum of squares")

kc <- kmeans(nor, 5)
kc
